  "text": "Posterior reversible encephalopathy (PRE) may also be linked to sepsis and infection. [CITATION_1] In a study of 106 patients with PRE, 23.6% had infection or sepsis/septic shock. The clinical symptoms included altered mental status, seizures and visual disturbances. PRE was not an early finding, as it occurred up to 30 days after infection.",
